stling Federation of Pakistan, with [[PWFP Rumble in Pakistan|Rumble in Pakistan]] being the first.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/574608-karachi-to-host-world-wrestling-champions-contest-on-dec-21|title=Karachi to host World Wrestling Champions\u2019 contest on Dec 21|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nThe card consisted of nine matches including the main event for the inaugural [[PWFP World Heavyweight Championship]] between [[Rhyno]], Jordan, [[Matt Cross (wrestler)|Matt Cross]], Danny, RJ Faddy and Low Rider in a 6-men ladder match.\n\n== Event ==\n\n==== Pre-Conference ====\nIn November 2019, PWFP held a press conference. Pro Wrestling Federation of Pakistan's chairman Nauman Suleman and Pro Wrestling Federation of Pakistan's executive vice president Kamran Mughal attended the press conference along with Dreamworld Resort's Head of Marketing Faraz-al-Huda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brecorder.com/2019/11/25/547327/famous-foreign-wrestlers-to-compete-in-karachi-event/|title=Famous foreign wrestlers to compete in Karachi event|last=Shafa|first=Muhammad|date=2019-11-25|website=Business Recorder|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> PWFP superstars Jordan, Danny, AA Junior and others had also attended the press. In the press conference, it was announced that there would be a PWFP World Heavyweight Championship Qualifying Tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://propakistani.pk/2019/11/25/wrestling-champions-alberto-del-rio-rhino-coming-to-pakistan/|title=Wrestling Champions Alberto Del Rio & Rhino Coming to Pakistan|last=Staff|first=ProPK|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> On 1 December 2019, The PWFP World Heavyweight Championship Qualifying Tournament took place in the PWFP Complex. Jordan, Danny and RJ Faddy had won their matches and had qualified for the six-men ladder match at 2019 World Wrestling Champions. \n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; margin: 0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;